<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-10T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-10T09:00:00-05:00" n="840" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d840">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/1898: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-10T16:00:00+02:00">August 10,
                                    1943—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received August 10—11:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>5235. In accordance with the Department’s 4767, August 7, 5 p.m., I
                            informed Mr. Eden of the decision not to issue the proposed joint
                            statement regarding Palestine. He and Colonel Stanley<note n="87" xml:id="d840fn87">Col. Oliver Stanley, British Colonial
                                Secretary.</note> were both very disappointed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>